oad metadata, prepare image, delegate to provider, update metadata\n33:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n34:   - Verify: Returns `Dict[str, Any]` with agent info\n35: \n36: - [x] **T2.2** Implement `_prepare_image_for_publishing()` dispatcher\n37:   - Route to `_prepare_local_image()` or `_prepare_cloud_image()` based on `metadata.build_mode`\n38:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n39:   - Verify: Correct routing logic\n40: \n41: - [x] **T2.3** Implement `_prepare_local_image()` for local build mode\n42:   - Validate `image_url` is provided\n43:   - Push image to registry using `DockerService.push_image()` if credentials available\n44:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n45:   - Verify: Returns `image_url`, pushes image when credentials provided\n46: \n47: - [x] **T2.4** Implement `_prepare_cloud_image()` for cloud build mode\n48:   - Construct image URL from `cloud_provider`, `agent_name`, `version`\n49:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n50:   - Verify: Returns formatted image URL string\n51: \n52: - [x] **T2.5** Implement `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` for AgentCube provider\n53:   - Create `AgentCubeProvider` instance\n54:   - Deploy `AgentRuntime` CR with required fields: `workloadManagerURL`, `routerURL`, readiness probe\n55:   - Generate `session_id`, `agent_id`\n56:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n57:   - Verify: Returns dict with `status`, `agent_name`, `namespace`, `session_id`, `agent_id`\n58: \n59: - [x] **T2.6** Implement `_publish_k8s()` for standard K8s provider\n60:   - Create `KubernetesProvider` instance\n61:   - Deploy `Deployment` + `Service` (optionally `NodePort`)\n62:   - Validate `node_port` range (30000-32767)\n63:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n64:   - Verify: Returns dict with deployment info\n65: \n66: - [x] **T2.7** Implement `_update_publish_metadata()` to persist publish results\n67:   - Update: `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`, `agent_endpoint`\n68:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n69:   - Verify: Metadata file updated after publish\n70: \n71: - [x] **T2.8** Implement `_generate_session_id()` helper\n72:   - Generate 32-character alphanumeric string using `secrets.choice()`\n73:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n74:   - Verify: Returns unique ID on each call\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ## Phase 3: Provider Services Ō£ō\n79: \n80: - [x] **T3.1** Implement `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()`\n81:   - Create/replace `AgentRuntime` CR in K8s\n82:   - Handle 409 conflict (update existing)\n83:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n84:   - Verify: CR created/updated in cluster\n85: \n86: - [x] **T3.2** Implement `AgentCubeProvider._sanitize_name()` for K8s naming rules\n87:   - Lowercase, replace non-alphanumeric with `-`, max 63 chars\n88:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n89:   - Verify: Produces valid K8s resource names\n90: \n91: - [x] **T3.3** Implement `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` for standard K8s deployment\n92:   - Create `Deployment`, `Service` (ClusterIP or NodePort)\n93:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n94:   - Verify: Resources created in cluster\n95: \n96: - [x] **T3.4** Add error handling for missing K8s config\n97:   - Try kubeconfig, then in-cluster config\n98:   - Raise `RuntimeError` with helpful message if both fail\n99:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`, `k8s_provider.py`\n100:   - Verify: Clear error message when K8s unavailable\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## Phase 4: CLI Integration Ō£ō\n105: \n106: - [x] **T4.1** Add `publish` command to CLI with Typer\n107:   - All options from T1.3 as `@app.command()` parameters\n108:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n109:   - Verify: `agentcube publish --help` shows all options\n110: \n111: - [x] **T4.2** Implement CLI progress UI for publish\n112:   - Use `rich.progress` spinner during publish\n113:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n114:   - Verify: Spinner displays during operation\n115: \n116: - [x] **T4.3** Format and display publish results\n117:   - Show: `Agent ID`, `Endpoint`, `Namespace`, `Provider`\n118:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n119:   - Verify: Output is clear and readable\n120: \n121: - [x] **T4.4** Implement consistent error handling\n122:   - Use `_handle_error()` helper with verbose traceback option\n123:   - Exit code 1 on failure\n124:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n125:   - Verify: Errors display clearly, verbose mode shows traceback\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## Phase 5: Validation & Edge Cases\n130: \n131: - [ ] **T5.1** Validate `workload_manager_url` and `router_url` are present for `agentcube` provider\n132:   - Check metadata or environment variables\n133:   - Raise `ValueError` with helpful message if missing\n134:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n135:   - Verify: Clear error when URLs missing\n136: \n137: - [ ] **T5.2** Validate `node_port` range (30000-32767) for K8s provider\n138:   - Already implemented in `_publish_k8s()`, add CLI-level validation\n139:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n140:   - Verify: Rejects invalid ports before runtime call\n141: \n142: - [ ] **T5.3** Handle existing AgentRuntime CR gracefully (update vs create)\n143:   - Already implemented via 409 handling in `AgentCubeProvider`\n144:   - Add logging to indicate update vs create\n145:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n146:   - Verify: Logs indicate whether CR was created or updated\n147: \n148: - [ ] **T5.4** Handle image push failures gracefully\n149:   - Catch `DockerService` exceptions, re-raise with context\n150:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n151:   - Verify: Clear error message on push failure\n152: \n153: - [ ] **T5.5** Validate metadata file exists before publish\n154:   - Check for `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml`\n155:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n156:   - Verify: Early error if metadata missing\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ## Phase 6: Testing\n161: \n162: - [ ] **T6.1** Unit test `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()`\n163:   - Test with/without `image_url`, with/without credentials\n164:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n165:   - Verify: Correct image URL returned, push called when expected\n166: \n167: - [ ] **T6.2** Unit test `PublishRuntime._prepare_cloud_image()`\n168:   - Test various `cloud_provider`, `version` combinations\n169:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n170:   - Verify: Correct image URL format\n171: \n172: - [ ] **T6.3** Unit test `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()`\n173:   - Mock `AgentCubeProvider`, verify CR spec\n174:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n175:   - Verify: Correct provider call, session_id generated\n176: \n177: - [ ] **T6.4** Unit test `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s()`\n178:   - Mock `KubernetesProvider`, verify deployment params\n179:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n180:   - Verify: Correct provider call, node_port validated\n181: \n182: - [ ] **T6.5** Integration test: publish to K8s (mock cluster)\n183:   - Use `kind` or `kindless` K8s cluster\n184:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_publish_integration.py`\n185:   - Verify: CR/deployment created, metadata updated\n186: \n187: - [ ] **T6.6** CLI test: `agentcube publish --help`\n188:   - Verify all options documented\n189:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_cli.py`\n190:   - Verify: Help text accurate\n191: \n192: - [ ] **T6.7** Error case: missing `workload_manager_url`\n193:   - Verify clear error message\n194:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n195:   - Verify: `ValueError` raised with helpful message\n196: \n197: - [ ] **T6.8** Error case: invalid `node_port`\n198:   - Verify validation rejects out-of-range ports\n199:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n200:   - Verify: `ValueError` for invalid ports\n201: \n202: ---\n203: \n204: ## Phase 7: Documentation & Cleanup\n205: \n206: - [ ] **T7.1** Add docstrings to all public methods\n207:   - Follow Google/NumPy style\n208:   - File: All publish-related files\n209:   - Verify: `help()` displays correctly\n210: \n211: - [ ] **T7.2** Add type hints to all functions\n212:   - Use `typing` module for complex types\n213:   - File: All publish-related files\n214:   - Verify: `mypy` passes\n215: \n216: - [ ] **T7.3** Update README with publish command examples\n217:   - Show `agentcube publish --provider=agentcube` and `--provider=k8s`\n218:   - File: `cmd/cli/README.md`\n219:   - Verify: Examples are copy-paste runnable\n220: \n221: - [ ] **T7.4** Add troubleshooting section for common publish errors\n222:   - Missing URLs, image push failures, K8s config issues\n223:   - File: `cmd/cli/README.md` or `docs/cli/publish.md`\n224:   - Verify: Clear resolutions for each error\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## Acceptance Criteria\n229: \n230: 1. Ō£ģ `PublishRuntime` class fully implemented with all methods\n231: 2. Ō£ģ CLI `publish` command accepts all required options\n232: 3. Ō£ģ Two providers supported: `agentcube` (CR) and `k8s` (Deployment/Service)\n233: 4. Ō£ģ Image preparation works for both `local` and `cloud` build modes\n234: 5. Ō£ģ Metadata updated with publish results (`agent_id`, `session_id`, etc.)\n235: 6. Ō£ģ Error handling provides clear, actionable messages\n236: 7. ŌÅ│ Unit tests cover all publish runtime methods\n237: 8. ŌÅ│ Integration test validates end-to-end publish flow\n238: 9. ŌÅ│ Documentation includes examples and troubleshooting\n239: \n240: ---\n241: \n242: **Notes:**\n243: - Stage ST-3 is marked complete: runtime, providers, and CLI are implemented\n244: - Remaining work: comprehensive testing (Phase 6) and documentation (Phase 7)\n245: - Edge case validation (Phase 5) partially complete, needs CLI-level validation\n\n(End of file - total 245 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022 ŌĆö CLI Publish Command Tasks\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation & Models Ō£ō\n\n- [x] **T1.1** Define `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with publish-related fields\n  - Fields: `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`, `agent_endpoint`, `version`, `region`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/metadata_models.py`\n  - Verify: Model validates correctly with test fixtures\n\n- [x] **T1.2** Implement `MetadataService.load_metadata()` and `save_metadata()`\n  - Support multiple metadata file names: `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n  - Verify: Loads/saves metadata correctly in test workspace","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775869319201,"end":1775869319235}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869319239,"sessionID":"ses_285f1b8b7ffe1RxdyW3ql5Kl2g","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0f530a001ZA9fb54lQ1v9bT","messageID":"msg_d7a0f1101001e9AHKilXGu3wMP","sessionID":"ses_285f1b8b7ffe1RxdyW3ql5Kl2g","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_028dbd40273b41dd989aa3cc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-023/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-023/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status ÕæĮõ╗ż\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI toolkit to enable users to invoke deployed agents and check their status. These commands complete the core CLI workflow alongside existing `pack`, `build`, and `publish` commands.\n6: \n7: ## Scope\n8: \n9: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n10: **Language:** Python  \n11: **Size:** M\n12: \n13: This AR covers:\n14: - `invoke` command - POST JSON payloads to deployed agent endpoints\n15: - `status` command - Display agent deployment status in Rich table format\n16: - Support for two providers: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment/Service)\n17: - Header parsing and validation\n18: - Payload JSON parsing and validation\n19: - Session ID management\n20: \n21: ## Requirements\n22: \n23: ### Global Options\n24: \n25: Both commands inherit global options from the Typer app:\n26: - `--workspace` / `-f` - Workspace directory path (default: `\".\"`)\n27: - `--provider` - Target provider: `\"agentcube\"` or `\"k8s\"` (default: `\"agentcube\"`)\n28: - `--verbose` - Enable detailed logging (default: `False`)\n29: \n30: ### invoke Command\n31: \n32: **Signature:**\n33: ```python\n34: def invoke(\n35:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\"),\n36:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\"),\n37:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\"),\n38:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\"),\n39:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\"),\n40: ) -> None:\n41: ```\n42: \n43: **Behavior:**\n44: 1. Parse `payload` as JSON, exit with code 1 if invalid\n45: 2. Parse `header_list` into dict, validate `key:value` format\n46: 3. Load workspace metadata to get agent endpoint\n47: 4. Instantiate `InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n48: 5. Call `runtime.invoke(workspace_path, payload_dict, headers)`\n49: 6. Print response using Rich console\n50: 7. Handle errors via `_handle_error`\n51: \n52: **Header Format:**\n53: - Multiple `--header` flags allowed: `--header \"Authorization: Bearer token\"`\n54: - Must contain exactly one `:` separator\n55: - Format: `key:value` (whitespace trimmed)\n56: \n57: **Session Management:**\n58: - If metadata contains `session_id`, add header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n59: - User-provided headers take precedence\n60: \n61: ### status Command\n62: \n63: **Signature:**\n64: ```python\n65: def status(\n66:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\"),\n67:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\"),\n68:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\"),\n69: ) -> None:\n70: ```\n71: \n72: **Behavior:**\n73: 1. Load workspace metadata\n74: 2. Instantiate `StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n75: 3. Call `runtime.get_status(workspace_path, provider=provider)`\n76: 4. Display results in Rich Table\n77: 5. Exit with code 1 if status is `not_published` or `error`\n78: \n79: **Table Columns:**\n80: | Column | Description |\n81: |--------|-------------|\n82: | Property | Status property name |\n83: | Value | Property value |\n84: \n85: **Rows to Display:**\n86: - Agent Name\n87: - Status (published, not_published, error, running, etc.)\n88: - Agent ID (if available)\n89: - Agent Endpoint (if available)\n90: - Provider Type\n91: - Namespace\n92: - Additional provider-specific info\n93: \n94: ### Error Handling\n95: \n96: **Standard Errors:**\n97: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n98: |-------|-----------|---------|\n99: | Invalid JSON payload | 1 | \"Invalid payload JSON: {error}\" |\n100: | Invalid header format | 1 | \"Invalid header format. Expected 'key:value'\" |\n101: | Workspace not found | 1 | \"Workspace directory does not exist\" |\n102: | Not published | 1 | \"Agent not published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first\" |\n103: | Runtime error | 1 | \"Error {command}: {error}\" (with traceback if verbose) |\n104: \n105: **Helper Function:**\n106: ```python\n107: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n108:     \"\"\"Print error message and exit with code 1.\"\"\"\n109:     console = Console(stderr=True)\n110:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/]\")\n111:     if verbose:\n112:         console.print_exception()\n113:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n114: ```\n115: \n116: ## Implementation Details\n117: \n118: ### invoke Runtime Implementation\n119: \n120: **File:** `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n121: \n122: **Class Structure:**\n123: ```python\n124: class InvokeRuntime:\n125:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\"):\n126:         self.verbose = verbose\n127:         self.provider = provider\n128:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n129:     \n130:     def invoke(\n131:         self,\n132:         workspace_path: Path,\n133:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n134:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n135:     ) -> Any:\n136:         # Load metadata\n137:         # Validate prerequisites (agent_id, endpoint)\n138:         # Route to provider-specific invocation\n139:         # Return response\n140: ```\n141: \n142: **Provider-Specific Invocation:**\n143: \n144: **AgentCube Provider (AgentRuntime CR):**\n145: - Use `AgentCubeProvider` to get CR object\n146: - Construct URL: `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n147: - POST payload with `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n148: - Handle async HTTP request\n149: \n150: **Kubernetes Provider (Deployment/Service):**\n151: - Use `KubernetesProvider` to get deployment info\n152: - Get `service_url` from metadata (`http://localhost:{node_port}`)\n153: - POST payload directly to service URL\n154: \n155: ### status Runtime Implementation\n156: \n157: **File:** `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n158: \n159: **Class Structure:**\n160: ```python\n161: class StatusRuntime:\n162:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\"):\n163:         self.verbose = verbose\n164:         self.provider = provider\n165:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n166:     \n167:     def get_status(\n168:         self,\n169:         workspace_path: Path,\n170:         provider: Optional[str] = None,\n171:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n172:         # Load metadata\n173:         # Check if published (agent_id exists)\n174:         # Route to provider-specific status check\n175:         # Return status dict\n176: ```\n177: \n178: **Status Values:**\n179: | Status | Description |\n180: |--------|-------------|\n181: | `not_published` | No `agent_id` in metadata |\n182: | `running` | Deployment ready, pods healthy |\n183: | `error` | Deployment exists but not ready |\n184: | `unknown` | Cannot determine status |\n185: \n186: **AgentCube Provider Status:**\n187: - Query CR via `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime(name, namespace)`\n188: - Extract status from `cr_object[\"status\"]`\n189: - Fields: `status`, `agentEndpoint`, `phase`, `conditions`\n190: \n191: **Kubernetes Provider Status:**\n192: - Query Deployment via `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status(agent_name)`\n193: - Check replica availability and pod readiness\n194: - Fields: `replicas`, `ready_replicas`, `available_replicas`\n195: \n196: ### Provider Selection\n197: \n198: Both commands use the `--provider` flag to determine behavior:\n199: \n200: ```python\n201: if provider == \"agentcube\":\n202:     runtime = StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=\"agentcube\")\n203:     # Uses AgentCubeProvider internally\n204: elif provider == \"k8s\":\n205:     runtime = StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=\"k8s\")\n206:     # Uses KubernetesProvider internally\n207: else:\n208:     raise ValueError(f\"Unknown provider: {provider}\")\n209: ```\n210: \n211: ## File Changes\n212: \n213: ### Files to Create\n214: \n215: | File | Purpose |\n216: |------|---------|\n217: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | InvokeRuntime class |\n218: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | StatusRuntime class |\n219: \n220: ### Files to Modify\n221: \n222: | File | Changes |\n223: |------|---------|\n224: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Add `invoke` and `status` commands, register with Typer app |\n225: | `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Export new runtime classes |\n226: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Optionally export `StatusRuntime` |\n227: \n228: ### Dependencies\n229: \n230: Already available from existing implementation:\n231: - `MetadataService` - load workspace metadata\n232: - `AgentCubeProvider` - CR-based operations  \n233: - `KubernetesProvider` - standard K8s operations\n234: - `AgentMetadata` - Pydantic model\n235: - `rich` - console output and tables\n236: - `httpx` or `requests` - HTTP invocations\n237: \n238: ## Testing Strategy\n239: \n240: ### Unit Tests\n241: \n242: **test_invoke_command.py:**\n243: - Test header parsing (valid/invalid formats)\n244: - Test payload parsing (valid/invalid JSON)\n245: - Test command registration with Typer\n246: \n247: **test_status_command.py:**\n248: - Test status table rendering\n249: - Test exit codes for different statuses\n250: \n251: **test_invoke_runtime.py:**\n252: - Test `_validate_invoke_prerequisites`\n253: - Test provider selection logic\n254: - Test session ID header injection\n255: \n256: **test_status_runtime.py:**\n257: - Test `_get_cr_k8s_status` with mock CR\n258: - Test `_get_k8s_status` with mock deployment\n259: - Test status determination logic\n260: \n261: ### Integration Tests\n262: \n263: Mock external services:\n264: - Mock Kubernetes API responses\n265: - Mock HTTP endpoints for invocation\n266: - Test full command flow with mocked runtimes\n267: \n268: ## Acceptance Criteria\n269: \n270: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube invoke --help` shows correct options and descriptions\n271: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube status --help` shows correct options and descriptions\n272: - [ ] Invalid JSON payload exits with code 1 and red error message\n273: - [ ] Invalid header format exits with code 1 with guidance\n274: - [ ] Status command displays Rich table with agent info\n275: - [ ] Status exits with code 1 when `agent_id` is missing\n276: - [ ] Invoke command sends `x-agentcube-session-id` when metadata has `session_id`\n277: - [ ] Provider flag switches between `agentcube` and `k8s` behavior\n278: - [ ] Verbose mode shows full traceback on errors\n279: - [ ] All existing CLI tests continue to pass\n280: \n281: ## Implementation Checklist\n282: \n283: - [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` with InvokeRuntime class\n284: - [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` with StatusRuntime class\n285: - [ ] Add `invoke` command to `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n286: - [ ] Add `status` command to `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n287: - [ ] Register commands with Typer app\n288: - [ ] Implement header parsing and validation\n289: - [ ] Implement payload JSON parsing\n290: - [ ] Implement error handling with verbose mode\n291: - [ ] Update `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` exports\n292: - [ ] Write unit tests for runtime classes\n293: - [ ] Write integration tests for CLI commands\n294: - [ ] Verify against spec scenarios\n295: \n296: ## Risks & Mitigations\n297: \n298: | Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\n299: |------|--------|------------|\n300: | Kubernetes client not initialized | High | Clear error messages, check prerequisites in runtime |\n301: | Missing router_url/workload_manager_url | Medium | Validate in metadata loading, provide setup guidance |\n302: | Async invocation in sync CLI | Medium | Use `asyncio.run()` wrapper for async HTTP calls |\n303: | Session header naming inconsistency | Low | Follow SDK convention (`x-agentcube-session-id`) |\n304: \n305: ## References\n306: \n307: - `cli-toolkit/design.md` - CLI package layout and command signatures\n308: - `cli-toolkit/spec.md` - Detailed requirements and scenarios for invoke/status\n309: - `python-sdk/design.md` - SDK client patterns for invocation\n310: - `deployment/client-go.md` - CR API group/version/plural details\n311: - AR-022 proposal - Previous CLI command implementation pattern\n\n(End of file - total 311 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status ÕæĮõ╗ż\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI toolkit to enable users to invoke deployed agents and check their status. These commands complete the core CLI workflow alongside existing `pack`, `build`, and `publish` commands.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\nThis AR covers:\n- `invoke` command - POST JSON payloads to deployed agent endpoints\n- `status` command - Display agent deployment status in Rich table format\n- Support for two providers: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment/Service)\n- Header parsing and validation\n- Payload JSON parsing and validation\n- Session ID management\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-023/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775869319208,"end":1775869319237}}}}
