{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869457055,"sessionID":"ses_285f1b8b7ffe1RxdyW3ql5Kl2g","part":{"id":"prt_d7a107522001JgZ605PxwKOsVV","messageID":"msg_d7a1034fb001lz6P95u2oAjlaQ","sessionID":"ses_285f1b8b7ffe1RxdyW3ql5Kl2g","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_05fd40cc0c7c4a3a8a77fdba","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md","content":"# AR-023 ŌĆö CLI invoke/status Commands Tasks\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation & Models Ō£ō\n\n- [x] **T1.1** Define `InvokeRuntime` class structure\n  - Constructor with `verbose` and `provider` parameters\n  - Main `invoke()` method signature\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Class instantiates correctly with test fixtures\n\n- [x] **T1.2** Define `StatusRuntime` class structure\n  - Constructor with `verbose` and `provider` parameters\n  - Main `get_status()` method signature\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Class instantiates correctly with test fixtures\n\n- [x] **T1.3** Add runtime classes to `__init__.py` exports\n  - Export `InvokeRuntime` and `StatusRuntime`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n  - Verify: Imports work from `agentcube.runtime`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Invoke Runtime Implementation Ō£ō\n\n- [x] **T2.1** Implement `InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites()`\n  - Load metadata, validate `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint` exists\n  - Extract endpoint from metadata (`agent_endpoint` or `k8s_deployment.service_url`)\n  - Extract namespace from deployment info\n  - Return tuple: `(metadata, endpoint, namespace)`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Raises `ValueError` if not published, returns correct tuple\n\n- [x] **T2.2** Implement `InvokeRuntime.invoke()` main method\n  - Call `_validate_invoke_prerequisites()` to get endpoint\n  - For `agentcube` provider with `AgentRuntime` CR: construct invocation URL\n  - Inject `session_id` into headers if present in metadata\n  - Route to appropriate invocation method based on provider\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Correct URL construction, session header injection\n\n- [x] **T2.3** Implement `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube()`\n  - Async HTTP POST to endpoint with payload and headers\n  - Use `httpx.AsyncClient` with 60s timeout\n  - Parse JSON response\n  - Handle non-HTTP endpoints gracefully\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Returns JSON response, handles errors\n\n- [x] **T2.4** Implement `InvokeRuntime._direct_http_invocation()`\n  - Async HTTP POST for standard K8s deployments\n  - Use `httpx.AsyncClient` with 60s timeout\n  - Return JSON response dict\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Returns correct response format\n\n- [x] **T2.5** Implement fallback logic for endpoint failures\n  - Try agentcube invocation first, fallback to direct HTTP\n  - Handle invalid endpoint formats gracefully\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Fallback works when primary fails\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Status Runtime Implementation Ō£ō\n\n- [x] **T3.1** Implement `StatusRuntime.get_status()` main method\n  - Load metadata, check if published\n  - Route to provider-specific status getter\n  - Return consistent status dict structure\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Returns correct status dict for different scenarios\n\n- [x] **T3.2** Implement `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()` for AgentRuntime CR\n  - Use `AgentCubeProvider` to query CR\n  - Extract status from `cr_object[\"status\"]`\n  - Return fields: `status`, `provider`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `agent_endpoint`, `message`\n  - Handle CR not found case