- Display success message with JSON response\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Spinner displays, output formatted clearly\n\n- [x] **T4.5** Add `status` command to CLI with Typer\n  - Options: `workspace`, `provider`, `verbose`\n  - Default provider: `\"agentcube\"`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: `agentcube status --help` shows all options\n\n- [x] **T4.6** Implement `status` command progress UI\n  - Use `rich.progress` spinner during status fetch\n  - Check for `not_published` or `error` status\n  - Exit with code 1 and helpful message for those cases\n  - Display status details as key-value pairs\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Clear status output, correct exit codes\n\n- [x] **T4.7** Implement consistent error handling for both commands\n  - Use `_handle_error()` helper with verbose traceback option\n  - Exit code 1 on failure\n  - Red error messages with context\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Errors display clearly, verbose mode shows traceback\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Validation & Edge Cases\n\n- [ ] **T5.1** Validate `router_url` is present for AgentRuntime CR invocation\n  - Check metadata for `router_url` when provider is `agentcube`\n  - Raise `ValueError` with helpful message if missing\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Clear error when router_url missing\n\n- [ ] **T5.2** Validate header format more strictly\n  - Check for empty key or value after split\n  - Warn about duplicate headers\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Rejects `:value` or `key:` formats\n\n- [ ] **T5.3** Add timeout handling with clear error messages\n  - Catch `httpx.TimeoutException` separately\n  - Display \"Request timed out after Xs\" message\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Timeout shows clear message, not stack trace\n\n- [ ] **T5.4** Validate workspace path exists before invocation\n  - Check `workspace_path.exists()` early\n  - Raise helpful error if directory missing\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Verify: Early error for non-existent workspace\n\n- [ ] **T5.5** Handle HTTP error codes gracefully\n  - Catch `httpx.HTTPStatusError` with status code\n  - Display status code and response body\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Clear error on 4xx/5xx responses\n\n- [ ] **T5.6** Log invocation details in verbose mode\n  - Log endpoint URL, payload size, headers (excluding sensitive)\n  - Log response status code and size\n  - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Debug logs appear with `--verbose`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Testing\n\n- [ ] **T6.1** Unit test `InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites()`\n  - Test with published agent (has `agent_id`)\n  - Test with unpublished agent (no `agent_id`)\n  - Test with endpoint but no agent_id\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_invoke_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Correct validation, appropriate errors\n\n- [ ] **T6.2** Unit test `InvokeRuntime.invoke()` with mock HTTP\n  - Mock `httpx.AsyncClient.post()`\n  - Test session_id header injection\n  - Test payload passing\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_invoke_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Correct HTTP call, headers included\n\n- [ ] **T6.3** Unit test `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube()`\n  - Test successful response\n  - Test HTTP error response\n  - Test timeout handling\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_invoke_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Response parsing, error propagation\n\n- [ ] **T6.4** Unit test `StatusRuntime.get_status()` scenarios\n  - Test not_published case\n  - Test successful status retrieval\n  - Test error case\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_status_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Correct status dict returned\n\n- [ ] **T6.5** Unit test `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()`\n  - Mock `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime()`\n  - Test CR with status subresource\n  - Test CR without status subresource\n  - Test CR not found\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_status_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Correct status extraction\n\n- [ ] **T6.6** Unit test `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status()`\n  - Mock `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()`\n  - Test with ready replicas\n  - Test with partial ready replicas\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_status_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Replica counts correct\n\n- [ ] **T6.7** CLI test: `invoke` command header parsing\n  - Test valid headers: `--header \"Authorization: Bearer token\"`\n  - Test invalid headers: `--header \"invalid\"`\n  - Test multiple headers\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_cli.py`\n  - Verify: Headers parsed correctly, errors on invalid\n\n- [ ] **T6.8** CLI test: `invoke` command payload parsing\n  - Test valid JSON: `--payload '{\"key\": \"value\"}'`\n  - Test invalid JSON: `--payload 'not json'`\n  - Test empty payload: `--payload '{}'`\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_cli.py`\n  - Verify: JSON parsed, errors on invalid\n\n- [ ] **T6.9** CLI test: `status` command output\n  - Test published agent status display\n  - Test not_published exit code and message\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_cli.py`\n  - Verify: Output format, exit codes\n\n- [ ] **T6.10** Integration test: invoke against mock server\n  - Use `httpx-mock` or test HTTP server\n  - Test full invoke flow with mocked endpoint\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_invoke_integration.py`\n  - Verify: End-to-end invoke works\n\n- [ ] **T6.11** Integration test: status against mock K8s\n  - Mock K8s API responses\n  - Test status retrieval flow\n  - File: `cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_status_integration.py`\n  - Verify: End-to-end status works\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: Documentation & Cleanup\n\n- [ ] **T7.1** Add docstrings to all public methods\n  - Follow Google/NumPy style\n  - Document args, returns, raises\n  - File: `invoke_runtime.py`, `status_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: `help()` displays correctly\n\n- [ ] **T7.2** Add type hints to all functions\n  - Use `typing` m